(upos) are those long-term commitments that are noncancelable or cancelable
only under certain conditions, and that third parties have used to secure
financing for the facilities that will provide the contracted goods or
services. the undiscounted obligations of $1,095 million mainly pertain to
pipeline throughput agreements and include $433 million of obligations to
equity companies.
