the gross unrecognized tax benefit
balances shown above are predominantly related to tax positions that would
reduce the corporations effective tax rate if the positions are favorably
resolved. unfavorable resolution of these tax positions generally would not
increase the effective tax rate. the 2014, 2013 and 2012 changes in
unrecognized tax benefits did not have a material effect on the corporations
net income.
resolution of these tax positions through negotiations with
the relevant tax authorities or through litigation will take many years to
complete. it is difficult to predict the timing of resolution for tax positions
since such timing is not entirely within the control of the corporation. it is
reasonably possible that the total amount of unrecognized tax benefits could
increase by up to 30percent in the next 12 months, with no material
impact on the corporations net income.
