operating statistics include 100 percent
of operations of majority-owned subsidiaries; for other companies, crude
production, gas, petroleum product and chemical prime product sales include
exxonmobils ownership percentage and refining throughput includes quantities
processed for exxonmobil. net production excludes royalties and quantities due
others when produced, whether payment is made in kind or cash.
(1) gas converted to oil-equivalent at
6million cubic feet = 1thousand barrels.
(2) petroleum product sales data
reported net of purchases/sales contracts with the same counterparty.
(3) prime product sales are total
product sales excluding carbon black oil and sulfur. prime product sales
include exxonmobils share of equity company volumes and finished-product
transfers to the downstream.
